The Biblical Lexicon Development Project (BLDP) is a theological and linguistic initiative designed to create a comprehensive, root-anchored biblical lexicon that prioritizes original Hebrew, Aramaic, and Greek meanings with theological clarity for modern readers.\
\
This project emphasizes semantic precision, covenantal coherence, and linguistic integrity, ensuring that biblical terms are faithfully transmitted while uncovering their physical root meanings and conceptual frameworks. It seeks to avoid theological flattening and linguistic drift, restoring the vibrancy of the biblical text.\
\
I. Core Vision and Purpose\
\
